@precog・55 we had requests to give a bit more heads up when changes are coming.  Based on concerns expressed here and some tests we've done we've decided to increase both the Alpha parameter  to 0.1, which determines how impactful more recent evaluations are, and the reduce the Decay parameter to 0.8, which determines how big a share top miners get in a single epoch.  Both these changes should push more rewards to top performing miners over time.

We agree that we want to focus on good rewards for the top few miners, and the incentive curve has indeed flattened since our changes two weeks ago.  After running some tests we feel both these parameters in conjunction will give a significantly higher fraction of rewards to the top 10-20 miners over time.  

We plan to push these changes tomorrow morning, and will monitor how the incentives shift over the next few days

